  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the project is to help increase knowledge and awareness of Danish design students and consumers about the generally poor
labor and human rights conditions of the textile workers in Asia and how sustainable clothing design can improve conditions for the workers. 

The project will eventually help to push the Danish fashion industry in a more sustainable direction and create a greater demand among consumers for sustainable clothing design. Thus the project will help to improve conditions for workers while strengthening the competitiveness of the Danish fashion industry. The 3-year project was granted in December 2013.</narrative>
  </description>
